                  R Programming Basics
R has 5 basic datatypes:
1)Numeric
2)Integer
3)Character
4)Complex
5)Logical

Vectors -
A vector has same data type.
A vector is created using : 
vectorname <- c(vector items)

To combine vectors the vectors must be of the same size / length.
Combining vectors using functions:
cbind() - Column Bind
rbind() - Row Bind 

Lists - 
List can have variety of data types

A list is created using :
listname = list(list items)

A list can contain a vector inside it.
Individual element of a list is accessed using listname[position]



Data Frames -
Are used to store tables.
Different from matrix.
Can have different classes.


